# 2. Weaponization: 
 - Methods of preparation aimed at setting up the required infrastructure for the attack.
  - Intruder develops malware designed to exploit the vulnerability
  - Intruder creates remote access malware weapon, such as a virus or worm, tailored to one or more vulnerabilities.
   - Viruses
   - Ransomware
   - Worms
   - Trojans
   - Rootkits
   - Keyloggers
   - Logic bombs
   - Adware
   - Spyware
   - Bots
